<Layout title="The Ultimate Dress Shirt Guide - Classic Menswear Chronicle">
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-8">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6">The Ultimate Dress Shirt Guide</h1>
    
    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1620799140408-edc6dcb6d633?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1000&q=80" alt="Various dress shirts" class="w-full h-64 object-cover mb-6 rounded-lg">
    
    <p class="text-xl mb-6">A well-fitted dress shirt is a cornerstone of any gentleman's wardrobe. This comprehensive guide will help you understand the various aspects of dress shirts, from fabrics and styles to care and maintenance.</p>
    
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">1. Dress Shirt Fabrics</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">The choice of fabric affects the shirt's appearance, comfort, and durability.</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6">
      <li>Cotton: Most common, breathable, and easy to care for</li>
      <li>Linen: Lightweight and breathable, perfect for summer</li>
      <li>Oxford cloth: Durable and slightly more casual</li>
      <li>Poplin: Smooth and crisp, ideal for formal settings</li>
      <li>Twill: Soft and wrinkle-resistant</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">2. Collar Styles</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">The collar is one of the most noticeable features of a dress shirt.</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6">
      <li>Point collar: Most common, versatile for various tie knots</li>
      <li>Spread collar: Wider space between points, suits larger tie knots</li>
      <li>Button-down collar: More casual, great for business casual looks</li>
      <li>Wing collar: Formal, typically worn with tuxedos</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">3. Cuff Styles</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">Cuffs add a finishing touch to your shirt sleeves.</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6">
      <li>Barrel cuffs: Most common, fastened with buttons</li>
      <li>French cuffs: More formal, require cufflinks</li>
      <li>Convertible cuffs: Can be worn with buttons or cufflinks</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">4. Fit and Sizing</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">A well-fitted shirt enhances your appearance and comfort.</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6">
      <li>Collar size: Should allow for two fingers to fit comfortably</li>
      <li>Shoulder seams: Should align with the edge of your shoulders</li>
      <li>Sleeve length: Should end at the base of your thumb when cuffs are unbuttoned</li>
      <li>Body fit: Slim, regular, or relaxed, depending on your preference and body type</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">5. Care and Maintenance</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">Proper care ensures your dress shirts look great and last longer.</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6">
      <li>Follow care label instructions</li>
      <li>Wash in cold water to prevent shrinkage</li>
      <li>Iron or steam to remove wrinkles</li>
      <li>Store on hangers to maintain shape</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Choosing the Right Dress Shirt</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">Consider these factors when selecting a dress shirt:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6">
      <li>The occasion or dress code</li>
      <li>Your body type and personal style</li>
      <li>The season and climate</li>
      <li>Compatibility with your existing wardrobe</li>
    </ul>
    
    <p class="mb-6">For more advice on building a versatile wardrobe, check out our guide on <a href="/blog/building-a-classic-wardrobe" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">building a classic wardrobe</a>.</p>
    
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Conclusion</h2>
    <p class="mb-6">A well-chosen dress shirt can elevate your entire outfit. By understanding the various aspects of dress shirts, from fabrics and styles to fit and care, you'll be able to make informed choices and always look your best.</p>
    
    <p>For more in-depth information on menswear, explore our <a href="/blog" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">blog</a> and other <a href="/guides" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">style guides</a>.</p>
  </article>
</Layout>